    {
      "id": "el_30",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 62,
      "y": 1257,
      "width": 370,
      "height": 18,
      "text": "Remainder-based Problems",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 14,
      "strokeColor": "#7048e8",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 3000,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 30,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_1_3"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Remainder-based Problems",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_31",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 62,
      "y": 1279,
      "width": 406,
      "height": 312,
      "text": "Largest number dividing X,Y,Z leaving remainder R:\n  = HCF(X-R, Y-R, Z-R)\n\nLargest number dividing X,Y leaving remainders a,b:\n  = HCF(X-a, Y-b)\n\nSmallest number divisible by X,Y,Z:\n  = LCM(X, Y, Z)\n\nSmallest number ÷ X,Y,Z leaves remainder R:\n  = LCM(X, Y, Z) + R\n\nSmallest number ÷ X,Y,Z leaves remainders a,b,c:\n  (X-a)=(Y-b)=(Z-c)=k → LCM(X,Y,Z) - k\n\nWHY: Subtracting remainder makes number exactly\n  divisible, so the answer divides all (X-R) values.\n\nEx: Largest N dividing 25,45 leaving rem 1:\n  HCF(24,44)=4. Check: 25/4=6r1✓ 45/4=11r1✓",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 3100,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 31,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_1_3"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Largest number dividing X,Y,Z leaving remainder R:\n  = HCF(X-R, Y-R, Z-R)\n\nLargest number dividing X,Y leaving remainders a,b:\n  = HCF(X-a, Y-b)\n\nSmallest number divisible by X,Y,Z:\n  = LCM(X, Y, Z)\n\nSmallest number ÷ X,Y,Z leaves remainder R:\n  = LCM(X, Y, Z) + R\n\nSmallest number ÷ X,Y,Z leaves remainders a,b,c:\n  (X-a)=(Y-b)=(Z-c)=k → LCM(X,Y,Z) - k\n\nWHY: Subtracting remainder makes number exactly\n  divisible, so the answer divides all (X-R) values.\n\nEx: Largest N dividing 25,45 leaving rem 1:\n  HCF(24,44)=4. Check: 25/4=6r1✓ 45/4=11r1✓",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
