    {
      "id": "el_66",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 62,
      "y": 2613,
      "width": 170,
      "height": 18,
      "text": "LCM and HCF",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 14,
      "strokeColor": "#7048e8",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 6600,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 66,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_3_3"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "LCM and HCF",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_67",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 62,
      "y": 2635,
      "width": 297,
      "height": 219,
      "text": "LCM x HCF = Product of two numbers\nLCM = (a x b) / HCF\nHCF = (a x b) / LCM\n\nHCF = lowest powers of common primes\nLCM = highest powers of ALL primes\nHCF always divides LCM\nFor co-primes: HCF=1, LCM=a x b\n\nWHY: If a=HCF×m, b=HCF×n (m,n coprime)\n  LCM=HCF×m×n, so HCF×LCM=HCF²×m×n=a×b\n\nEx: a=12, b=18 → HCF=6, LCM=36\n  6×36=216=12×18 ✓",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 6700,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 67,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_3_3"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "LCM x HCF = Product of two numbers\nLCM = (a x b) / HCF\nHCF = (a x b) / LCM\n\nHCF = lowest powers of common primes\nLCM = highest powers of ALL primes\nHCF always divides LCM\nFor co-primes: HCF=1, LCM=a x b\n\nWHY: If a=HCF×m, b=HCF×n (m,n coprime)\n  LCM=HCF×m×n, so HCF×LCM=HCF²×m×n=a×b\n\nEx: a=12, b=18 → HCF=6, LCM=36\n  6×36=216=12×18 ✓",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
