    {
      "id": "el_96",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 542,
      "y": 3667,
      "width": 415,
      "height": 17,
      "text": "Consecutive / Series Formulas",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#2f9e44",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 9600,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 96,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_5_1"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Consecutive / Series Formulas",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_97",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 542,
      "y": 3689,
      "width": 367,
      "height": 188,
      "text": "First n natural nos: Avg = (n+1)/2\nFirst n even nos:    Avg = n+1\nFirst n odd nos:     Avg = n\n\nAny AP: Avg = (First + Last) / 2\nSquares of 1..n: Avg = (n+1)(2n+1)/6\n\nWHY: In any AP, values are symmetric around\nthe middle, so Avg = midpoint = (First+Last)/2.\n\nEx: First 5 natural: Avg=(5+1)/2=3\n  Check: (1+2+3+4+5)/5 = 15/5 = 3 ✓",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 9700,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 97,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_5_1"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "First n natural nos: Avg = (n+1)/2\nFirst n even nos:    Avg = n+1\nFirst n odd nos:     Avg = n\n\nAny AP: Avg = (First + Last) / 2\nSquares of 1..n: Avg = (n+1)(2n+1)/6\n\nWHY: In any AP, values are symmetric around\nthe middle, so Avg = midpoint = (First+Last)/2.\n\nEx: First 5 natural: Avg=(5+1)/2=3\n  Check: (1+2+3+4+5)/5 = 15/5 = 3 ✓",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_98",
