    {
      "id": "el_114",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 62,
      "y": 4307,
      "width": 293,
      "height": 18,
      "text": "Basic Age Equations",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 14,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 11400,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 114,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_6_0"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Basic Age Equations",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_115",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 62,
      "y": 4329,
      "width": 351,
      "height": 203,
      "text": "Present age = x\nAge t years ago = x - t\nAge t years hence = x + t\n\nIf ratio of ages a:b → ages = ak, bk\nDifference of ages stays CONSTANT\nSum of ages increases by 2t after t yrs\n\nWHY: Both people age equally, so the gap\nbetween them never changes — only sum grows.\n\nEx: A=30, B=20 → Diff=10 (always 10)\n  After 5 yrs: 35,25 → Diff=10, Sum=60=50+2×5",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 11500,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 115,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_6_0"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Present age = x\nAge t years ago = x - t\nAge t years hence = x + t\n\nIf ratio of ages a:b → ages = ak, bk\nDifference of ages stays CONSTANT\nSum of ages increases by 2t after t yrs\n\nWHY: Both people age equally, so the gap\nbetween them never changes — only sum grows.\n\nEx: A=30, B=20 → Diff=10 (always 10)\n  After 5 yrs: 35,25 → Diff=10, Sum=60=50+2×5",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
