      "width": 351,
      "height": 219,
      "text": "If A:B = m:n and diff = d\n  A = m×d/(m-n), B = n×d/(m-n)\n\nIf ratio was m:n, becomes p:q after t yrs\n  (mk+t)/(nk+t) = p/q → solve for k\n\nProduct of ages = P\n  Use factorization + constraints\n\nWHY: Ratio a:b means ages are multiples of k.\nDiff = (m-n)k, so k = diff / (ratio gap).\n\nEx: A:B=5:3, Diff=12 → k=12/(5-3)=6\n  A=30, B=18",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 11800,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 118,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_6_1"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "If A:B = m:n and diff = d\n  A = m×d/(m-n), B = n×d/(m-n)\n\nIf ratio was m:n, becomes p:q after t yrs\n  (mk+t)/(nk+t) = p/q → solve for k\n\nProduct of ages = P\n  Use factorization + constraints\n\nWHY: Ratio a:b means ages are multiples of k.\nDiff = (m-n)k, so k = diff / (ratio gap).\n\nEx: A:B=5:3, Diff=12 → k=12/(5-3)=6\n  A=30, B=18",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
