    {
      "id": "el_129",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 62,
      "y": 4947,
      "width": 247,
      "height": 18,
      "text": "Core Definitions",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 14,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 12900,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 129,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_7_0"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Core Definitions",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_130",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 62,
      "y": 4969,
      "width": 336,
      "height": 203,
      "text": "Boat speed in still water = B\nStream (current) speed = S\n\nDownstream speed = B + S  (current helps)\nUpstream speed   = B - S  (current opposes)\n\n──→ Boat ──→ Stream = DOWNSTREAM\n──→ Boat ←── Stream = UPSTREAM\n\nWHY: Current adds to boat's speed\n  going with it, subtracts against.\n\nEx: B=10, S=3 → Down=13, Up=7",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 13000,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 130,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_7_0"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Boat speed in still water = B\nStream (current) speed = S\n\nDownstream speed = B + S  (current helps)\nUpstream speed   = B - S  (current opposes)\n\n──→ Boat ──→ Stream = DOWNSTREAM\n──→ Boat ←── Stream = UPSTREAM\n\nWHY: Current adds to boat's speed\n  going with it, subtracts against.\n\nEx: B=10, S=3 → Down=13, Up=7",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_131",
      "type": "rectangle",
      "x": 530,
      "y": 4939,
      "width": 460,
      "height": 267,
      "strokeColor": "#2f9e44",
