    {
      "id": "el_186",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 62,
      "y": 7261,
      "width": 401,
      "height": 18,
      "text": "Alternate / Interval Pipes",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 14,
      "strokeColor": "#7048e8",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 18600,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 186,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_10_3"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Alternate / Interval Pipes",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_187",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 62,
      "y": 7283,
      "width": 289,
      "height": 219,
      "text": "Pipes work in alternate hours:\nWork in 2-hr cycle = 1/a + 1/b\n\nPipes work in intervals:\nNet work per cycle × number of cycles\nCheck for partial last cycle\n\nWHY: Each cycle contributes a fixed\n  fraction. Divide 1 by cycle-work\n  to find number of full cycles.\n\nEx: A=4h, B=6h, alternate hrs\n  Cycle=1/4+1/6=5/12. Full in\n  12/5=2.4 cycles ≈ 5 hrs",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 18700,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 187,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_10_3"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Pipes work in alternate hours:\nWork in 2-hr cycle = 1/a + 1/b\n\nPipes work in intervals:\nNet work per cycle × number of cycles\nCheck for partial last cycle\n\nWHY: Each cycle contributes a fixed\n  fraction. Divide 1 by cycle-work\n  to find number of full cycles.\n\nEx: A=4h, B=6h, alternate hrs\n  Cycle=1/4+1/6=5/12. Full in\n  12/5=2.4 cycles ≈ 5 hrs",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
