    {
      "id": "el_195",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 542,
      "y": 7614,
      "width": 278,
      "height": 18,
      "text": "Efficiency & Ratio",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 14,
      "strokeColor": "#2f9e44",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 19500,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 195,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_11_1"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Efficiency & Ratio",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_196",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 542,
      "y": 7636,
      "width": 312,
      "height": 297,
      "text": "EFFICIENCY RATIO:\n\"A is 2× efficient as B\" means:\n  A=2 units/day, B=1 unit/day\n  B=18 days → A=18/2=9 days\n  Eff ratio A:B = 2:1\n  Time ratio A:B = 1:2 (INVERSE!)\n\nWAGES: Split by EFFICIENCY\n  A(eff=3) B(eff=2), wage Rs.5000\n  A=3/5×5000=Rs.3000 ✓\n\nHalf eff → Double time\nDouble eff → Half time\n\nWHY: Work=Eff×Time. Same work →\n  Eff ∝ 1/Time (inverse relation).\n  Wages ∝ work done = eff × days worked.\n\nEx: A:B eff=3:1, B=18d → A=6d",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 19600,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 196,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_11_1"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "EFFICIENCY RATIO:\n\"A is 2× efficient as B\" means:\n  A=2 units/day, B=1 unit/day\n  B=18 days → A=18/2=9 days\n  Eff ratio A:B = 2:1\n  Time ratio A:B = 1:2 (INVERSE!)\n\nWAGES: Split by EFFICIENCY\n  A(eff=3) B(eff=2), wage Rs.5000\n  A=3/5×5000=Rs.3000 ✓\n\nHalf eff → Double time\nDouble eff → Half time\n\nWHY: Work=Eff×Time. Same work →\n  Eff ∝ 1/Time (inverse relation).\n  Wages ∝ work done = eff × days worked.\n\nEx: A:B eff=3:1, B=18d → A=6d",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
