    {
      "id": "el_198",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1022,
      "y": 7614,
      "width": 170,
      "height": 18,
      "text": "MDH Formula",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 14,
      "strokeColor": "#7048e8",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 19800,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 198,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_11_2"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "MDH Formula",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_199",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1022,
      "y": 7636,
      "width": 289,
      "height": 219,
      "text": "M1 × D1 × H1     M2 × D2 × H2\n─────────────  =  ─────────────\n     W1                W2\n\nMore Men → Less Days (inverse)\nMore Hours → Less Days (inverse)\nMore Work → More Days (direct)\n\nWHY: Total work = Men × Days × Hours.\n  Equal work means M1D1H1 = M2D2H2.\n  Different work → divide by W.\n\nEx: 5 men, 8 days, 6 hrs = 10 men,\n  ? days, 6 hrs → D2 = 5×8/10 = 4d",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 19900,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 199,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_11_2"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "M1 × D1 × H1     M2 × D2 × H2\n─────────────  =  ─────────────\n     W1                W2\n\nMore Men → Less Days (inverse)\nMore Hours → Less Days (inverse)\nMore Work → More Days (direct)\n\nWHY: Total work = Men × Days × Hours.\n  Equal work means M1D1H1 = M2D2H2.\n  Different work → divide by W.\n\nEx: 5 men, 8 days, 6 hrs = 10 men,\n  ? days, 6 hrs → D2 = 5×8/10 = 4d",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_200",
