    {
      "id": "el_208",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1022,
      "y": 8001,
      "width": 266,
      "height": 219,
      "text": "1/6d=4h   1/4d=6h   1/3d=8h\n1/2d=12h  2/3d=16h  3/4d=18h\n\nMen↔Women↔Children:\n  x Men = y Women = z Children\n  1 Man = z/x Children\n  Convert all to children + MDH\n\nWHY: 1 day=24h. Fraction × 24\n  gives hours. Conversions let you\n  use MDH with a single unit.\n\nEx: 2M=3W → 1M=1.5W.\n  6M+4W = 9W+4W = 13W",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 20800,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 208,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_11_5"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1/6d=4h   1/4d=6h   1/3d=8h\n1/2d=12h  2/3d=16h  3/4d=18h\n\nMen↔Women↔Children:\n  x Men = y Women = z Children\n  1 Man = z/x Children\n  Convert all to children + MDH\n\nWHY: 1 day=24h. Fraction × 24\n  gives hours. Conversions let you\n  use MDH with a single unit.\n\nEx: 2M=3W → 1M=1.5W.\n  6M+4W = 9W+4W = 13W",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
