    },
    {
      "id": "el_219",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1022,
      "y": 8332,
      "width": 370,
      "height": 18,
      "text": "Remove & Replace Formula",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 14,
      "strokeColor": "#e8590c",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 21900,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 219,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_12_2"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Remove & Replace Formula",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_220",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1022,
      "y": 8354,
      "width": 312,
      "height": 219,
      "text": "After n operations of removing x litres\nfrom V litres:\n\nFinal pure = V × (1 - x/V)^n\n\nConcentration after n replacements:\n= (1 - x/V)^n × 100%\n\nWHY: Each operation removes x/V fraction\nof whatever is left. After n ops the\nfraction remaining = (1-x/V)^n.\n\nEx: 80L milk, remove 8L twice:\n  80×(1-8/80)^2 = 80×(9/10)^2 = 64.8L",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 22000,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 220,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_12_2"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "After n operations of removing x litres\nfrom V litres:\n\nFinal pure = V × (1 - x/V)^n\n\nConcentration after n replacements:\n= (1 - x/V)^n × 100%\n\nWHY: Each operation removes x/V fraction\nof whatever is left. After n ops the\nfraction remaining = (1-x/V)^n.\n\nEx: 80L milk, remove 8L twice:\n  80×(1-8/80)^2 = 80×(9/10)^2 = 64.8L",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_221",
      "type": "rectangle",
      "x": 50,
