    {
      "id": "el_231",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 542,
      "y": 8971,
      "width": 278,
      "height": 18,
      "text": "Inverse Proportion",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 14,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 23100,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 231,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_13_1"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Inverse Proportion",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_232",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 542,
      "y": 8993,
      "width": 305,
      "height": 203,
      "text": "If A increases → B decreases (opposite)\nA₁/A₂ = B₂/B₁  (flip right side)\n\nMore men → Less days\nMore speed → Less time\nMore pipes → Less time to fill\n\nWHY: The product stays constant. Total\nwork = men × days. If men↑, days↓ to\nkeep product the same.\n\nEx: 12 men×10 days = 120 man-days\n  15 men × ? = 120 → ? = 8 days",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 23200,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 232,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_13_1"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "If A increases → B decreases (opposite)\nA₁/A₂ = B₂/B₁  (flip right side)\n\nMore men → Less days\nMore speed → Less time\nMore pipes → Less time to fill\n\nWHY: The product stays constant. Total\nwork = men × days. If men↑, days↓ to\nkeep product the same.\n\nEx: 12 men×10 days = 120 man-days\n  15 men × ? = 120 → ? = 8 days",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_233",
      "type": "rectangle",
      "x": 1010,
      "y": 8963,
      "width": 460,
      "height": 251,
      "strokeColor": "#e8590c",
