    },
    {
      "id": "el_244",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 62,
      "y": 9617,
      "width": 297,
      "height": 188,
      "text": "All invest for SAME duration\nProfit ratio = Capital ratio\n\nA:B = Cₐ : Cᵦ\nA's share = Profit × Cₐ/(Cₐ+Cᵦ)\n\nWHY: Same time means money is the only\ndifference. More capital = more risk\n= more profit share.\n\nEx: A=3000, B=5000, Profit=1600\n  Ratio=3:5, A=1600×3/8=600",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 24400,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 244,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_14_0"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "All invest for SAME duration\nProfit ratio = Capital ratio\n\nA:B = Cₐ : Cᵦ\nA's share = Profit × Cₐ/(Cₐ+Cᵦ)\n\nWHY: Same time means money is the only\ndifference. More capital = more risk\n= more profit share.\n\nEx: A=3000, B=5000, Profit=1600\n  Ratio=3:5, A=1600×3/8=600",
      "autoResize": true,
