    },
    {
      "id": "el_247",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 542,
      "y": 9617,
      "width": 273,
      "height": 188,
      "text": "Invest for DIFFERENT durations\nProfit ratio = Capital × Time ratio\n\nA:B = Cₐ×Tₐ : Cᵦ×Tᵦ\nA's share = Profit × (Cₐ×Tₐ)/Σ(C×T)\n\nWHY: Both capital AND time matter.\nRs.1000 for 6 months = Rs.6000 of\n\"capital-months\" of contribution.\n\nEx: A=4000×12=48k, B=6000×8=48k\n  Equal contribution → equal split",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 24700,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 247,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_14_1"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Invest for DIFFERENT durations\nProfit ratio = Capital × Time ratio\n\nA:B = Cₐ×Tₐ : Cᵦ×Tᵦ\nA's share = Profit × (Cₐ×Tₐ)/Σ(C×T)\n\nWHY: Both capital AND time matter.\nRs.1000 for 6 months = Rs.6000 of\n\"capital-months\" of contribution.\n\nEx: A=4000×12=48k, B=6000×8=48k\n  Equal contribution → equal split",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
