    },
    {
      "id": "el_253",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 62,
      "y": 9873,
      "width": 281,
      "height": 188,
      "text": "Split into periods at each change\nEffective capital = Σ(Cᵢ × Tᵢ)\n\nA invests C₁ for t₁, then C₂ for t₂\nA's effective = C₁×t₁ + C₂×t₂\nCompare effective capitals for ratio\n\nWHY: Different amounts for different\ndurations = sum of each segment.\n\nEx: 10k for 6mo + 15k for 6mo\n  Effective = 60k + 90k = 150k",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 25300,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 253,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_14_3"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Split into periods at each change\nEffective capital = Σ(Cᵢ × Tᵢ)\n\nA invests C₁ for t₁, then C₂ for t₂\nA's effective = C₁×t₁ + C₂×t₂\nCompare effective capitals for ratio\n\nWHY: Different amounts for different\ndurations = sum of each segment.\n\nEx: 10k for 6mo + 15k for 6mo\n  Effective = 60k + 90k = 150k",
      "autoResize": true,
