    {
      "id": "el_258",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 62,
      "y": 10173,
      "width": 386,
      "height": 18,
      "text": "Basic Percentage Formulas",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 14,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 25800,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 258,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_15_0"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Basic Percentage Formulas",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_259",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 62,
      "y": 10195,
      "width": 351,
      "height": 203,
      "text": "x% of y = (x/100) × y\nWhat % is X of Y = (X/Y) × 100\n\n% Increase = [(New-Old)/Old] × 100\n% Decrease = [(Old-New)/Old] × 100\n\nNew Value = Old × (1 ± %/100)\n\nWHY: \"Percent\" = per-hundred. We scale any\nfraction to a base of 100 for comparison.\n\nEx: 20% of 350 = (20/100)×350 = 70\n    What % is 42 of 168? = (42/168)×100 = 25%",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 25900,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 259,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_15_0"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "x% of y = (x/100) × y\nWhat % is X of Y = (X/Y) × 100\n\n% Increase = [(New-Old)/Old] × 100\n% Decrease = [(Old-New)/Old] × 100\n\nNew Value = Old × (1 ± %/100)\n\nWHY: \"Percent\" = per-hundred. We scale any\nfraction to a base of 100 for comparison.\n\nEx: 20% of 350 = (20/100)×350 = 70\n    What % is 42 of 168? = (42/168)×100 = 25%",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_260",
      "type": "rectangle",
      "x": 530,
      "y": 10165,
      "width": 460,
      "height": 298,
      "strokeColor": "#2f9e44",
      "backgroundColor": "#ebfbee",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 26000,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 260,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_15_1"
      ],
      "roundness": {
        "type": 3
      },
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_261",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 542,
      "y": 10173,
      "width": 432,
      "height": 18,
      "text": "Successive & Compound Change",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 14,
      "strokeColor": "#2f9e44",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 26100,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 261,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_15_1"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Successive & Compound Change",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_262",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 542,
      "y": 10195,
      "width": 351,
      "height": 250,
      "text": "Successive a% and b%:\n  Net = a + b + (a×b)/100 %\n\nPopulation growth (n yrs):\n  P × (1 + r/100)^n\n\nDepreciation (n yrs):\n  P × (1 - r/100)^n\n\n+x% then -x% = -(x²/100)% LOSS\n\nWHY: Second change applies on already-changed\nvalue, so cross-term (a×b)/100 appears.\n\nEx: +10% then +20%:\n  Net = 10+20+(10×20)/100 = 32%",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 26200,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 262,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_15_1"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Successive a% and b%:\n  Net = a + b + (a×b)/100 %\n\nPopulation growth (n yrs):\n  P × (1 + r/100)^n\n\nDepreciation (n yrs):\n  P × (1 - r/100)^n\n\n+x% then -x% = -(x²/100)% LOSS\n\nWHY: Second change applies on already-changed\nvalue, so cross-term (a×b)/100 appears.\n\nEx: +10% then +20%:\n  Net = 10+20+(10×20)/100 = 32%",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
