    {
      "id": "el_282",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 542,
      "y": 10844,
      "width": 293,
      "height": 18,
      "text": "Proportion Formulas",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 14,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 28200,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 282,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_16_1"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Proportion Formulas",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_283",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 542,
      "y": 10866,
      "width": 281,
      "height": 234,
      "text": "a:b = c:d → a×d = b×c\n(extremes product = means product)\n\nMean Proportional = √(a×c)\nThird Proportional = b²/a\nFourth Proportional = b×c/a\n\na:b :: c:d → a,d=extremes, b,c=means\n\nWHY: a/b = c/d, cross-multiply gives\na×d = b×c. Mean prop x satisfies\na/x = x/c, so x² = ac.\n\nEx: Mean prop of 4,9 = √(4×9) = 6\n    Check: 4:6 = 6:9 = 2:3 ✓",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 28300,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 283,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_16_1"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "a:b = c:d → a×d = b×c\n(extremes product = means product)\n\nMean Proportional = √(a×c)\nThird Proportional = b²/a\nFourth Proportional = b×c/a\n\na:b :: c:d → a,d=extremes, b,c=means\n\nWHY: a/b = c/d, cross-multiply gives\na×d = b×c. Mean prop x satisfies\na/x = x/c, so x² = ac.\n\nEx: Mean prop of 4,9 = √(4×9) = 6\n    Check: 4:6 = 6:9 = 2:3 ✓",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_284",
