    {
      "id": "el_285",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1022,
      "y": 10844,
      "width": 293,
      "height": 18,
      "text": "Dividing in a Ratio",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 14,
      "strokeColor": "#e8590c",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 28500,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 285,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_16_2"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Dividing in a Ratio",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_286",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1022,
      "y": 10866,
      "width": 305,
      "height": 250,
      "text": "Total T divided in ratio a:b:c\n\nA's share = [a/(a+b+c)] × T\nB's share = [b/(a+b+c)] × T\n\nFraction ratios 1/2 : 1/3 : 1/4\n→ LCM of 2,3,4 = 12\n→ 6 : 4 : 3\n\nWHY: Each part is a fraction of the\nwhole. Multiply fraction-ratios by\nLCM of denominators to clear fractions.\n\nEx: Rs.1300 in 2:3:8\n  1 part=1300/13=100\n  Shares: 200, 300, 800",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 28600,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 286,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_16_2"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Total T divided in ratio a:b:c\n\nA's share = [a/(a+b+c)] × T\nB's share = [b/(a+b+c)] × T\n\nFraction ratios 1/2 : 1/3 : 1/4\n→ LCM of 2,3,4 = 12\n→ 6 : 4 : 3\n\nWHY: Each part is a fraction of the\nwhole. Multiply fraction-ratios by\nLCM of denominators to clear fractions.\n\nEx: Rs.1300 in 2:3:8\n  1 part=1300/13=100\n  Shares: 200, 300, 800",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
