    {
      "id": "el_288",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 62,
      "y": 11162,
      "width": 247,
      "height": 18,
      "text": "Combining Ratios",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 14,
      "strokeColor": "#7048e8",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 28800,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 288,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_16_3"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Combining Ratios",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_289",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 62,
      "y": 11184,
      "width": 289,
      "height": 250,
      "text": "A:B = p:q and B:C = r:s\nA:B:C → LCM of q and r\n\nExample: A:B=2:3, B:C=4:5\nLCM(3,4)=12\nA:B=8:12, B:C=12:15\nA:B:C = 8:12:15\n\n4+ ratios: abc : xbc : xyc : xyz\n\nWHY: The common term (B) must be the\nsame number in both ratios. LCM makes\nB equal, then simply merge.\n\nEx: A:B=3:4, B:C=2:5 → LCM(4,2)=4\n  A:B=3:4, B:C=4:10 → 3:4:10",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 28900,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 289,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_16_3"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "A:B = p:q and B:C = r:s\nA:B:C → LCM of q and r\n\nExample: A:B=2:3, B:C=4:5\nLCM(3,4)=12\nA:B=8:12, B:C=12:15\nA:B:C = 8:12:15\n\n4+ ratios: abc : xbc : xyc : xyz\n\nWHY: The common term (B) must be the\nsame number in both ratios. LCM makes\nB equal, then simply merge.\n\nEx: A:B=3:4, B:C=2:5 → LCM(4,2)=4\n  A:B=3:4, B:C=4:10 → 3:4:10",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
