    {
      "id": "el_321",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 62,
      "y": 12535,
      "width": 436,
      "height": 15,
      "text": "True Discount & Banker's Discount",
      "fontSize": 12,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 12,
      "strokeColor": "#7048e8",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 32100,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 321,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_18_3"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "True Discount & Banker's Discount",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_322",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 62,
      "y": 12557,
      "width": 367,
      "height": 328,
      "text": "True Discount (TD):\n  TD = (Amount × Rate × Time) / (100 + RT)\n  Present Worth = Amount - TD\n  PW = Amount × 100 / (100 + RT)\n\nBanker's Discount (BD):\n  BD = Simple Interest on Amount\n  BD = (Amount × Rate × Time) / 100\n\nRelation:\n  BD - TD = SI on TD\n  BD = TD × (100 + RT) / 100\n  TD² = PW × BD\n\nWHY: TD = interest on Present Worth (PW).\n  BD = interest on full Amount (overestimates).\n  BD > TD always; difference = SI on TD.\n\nEx: Amt=1060, R=6%, T=1yr\n  PW=1060×100/106=1000, TD=60\n  BD=1060×6/100=63.60",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 32200,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 322,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_18_3"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "True Discount (TD):\n  TD = (Amount × Rate × Time) / (100 + RT)\n  Present Worth = Amount - TD\n  PW = Amount × 100 / (100 + RT)\n\nBanker's Discount (BD):\n  BD = Simple Interest on Amount\n  BD = (Amount × Rate × Time) / 100\n\nRelation:\n  BD - TD = SI on TD\n  BD = TD × (100 + RT) / 100\n  TD² = PW × BD\n\nWHY: TD = interest on Present Worth (PW).\n  BD = interest on full Amount (overestimates).\n  BD > TD always; difference = SI on TD.\n\nEx: Amt=1060, R=6%, T=1yr\n  PW=1060×100/106=1000, TD=60\n  BD=1060×6/100=63.60",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
