    {
      "id": "el_336",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 62,
      "y": 13362,
      "width": 339,
      "height": 18,
      "text": "Ratio & Chain Formulas",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 14,
      "strokeColor": "#7048e8",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 33600,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 336,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_19_3"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Ratio & Chain Formulas",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_337",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 62,
      "y": 13384,
      "width": 375,
      "height": 297,
      "text": "CP:SP = a:b\n  Profit% = (b-a)/a × 100  (b>a)\n  Loss% = (a-b)/a × 100  (a>b)\n\nSuccessive P% then L%:\n  Net = P - L - (P×L)/100\n\nChain: Manuf → Whole → Retail\n  Final = CP × (100+P1)/100 × (100+P2)/100 × ...\n\nBreak-even: Total SP = Total CP\n\nWHY: Ratio gives relative sizes directly.\n  P or L% always uses CP (=a) as base.\n  Chain = multiply all stage multipliers.\n\nEx: CP:SP=4:5 → P%=(5-4)/4×100=25%\n  Successive +20% then -10%:\n  Net=20-10-200/100=+8%",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 33700,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 337,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_19_3"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "CP:SP = a:b\n  Profit% = (b-a)/a × 100  (b>a)\n  Loss% = (a-b)/a × 100  (a>b)\n\nSuccessive P% then L%:\n  Net = P - L - (P×L)/100\n\nChain: Manuf → Whole → Retail\n  Final = CP × (100+P1)/100 × (100+P2)/100 × ...\n\nBreak-even: Total SP = Total CP\n\nWHY: Ratio gives relative sizes directly.\n  P or L% always uses CP (=a) as base.\n  Chain = multiply all stage multipliers.\n\nEx: CP:SP=4:5 → P%=(5-4)/4×100=25%\n  Successive +20% then -10%:\n  Net=20-10-200/100=+8%",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
