    {
      "id": "el_348",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1022,
      "y": 13793,
      "width": 324,
      "height": 18,
      "text": "Growth & Depreciation",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 14,
      "strokeColor": "#e8590c",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 34800,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 348,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_20_2"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Growth & Depreciation",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_349",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1022,
      "y": 13815,
      "width": 359,
      "height": 219,
      "text": "Population growth: P × (1 + R/100)^T\nDepreciation:      P × (1 - R/100)^T\n\nDifferent rates each year:\n  A = P × (1+R1/100) × (1+R2/100) × (1+R3/100)\n\nWHY: Growth compounds just like CI.\n  Depreciation = negative growth rate.\n  Different rates: chain-multiply each year.\n\nEx: Pop=10000, R=5%, T=2yr\n  =10000×(1.05)²=10000×1.1025=11025\nEx: Value=50000, depn=20%, T=2yr\n  =50000×(0.8)²=50000×0.64=32000",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 34900,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 349,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_20_2"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Population growth: P × (1 + R/100)^T\nDepreciation:      P × (1 - R/100)^T\n\nDifferent rates each year:\n  A = P × (1+R1/100) × (1+R2/100) × (1+R3/100)\n\nWHY: Growth compounds just like CI.\n  Depreciation = negative growth rate.\n  Different rates: chain-multiply each year.\n\nEx: Pop=10000, R=5%, T=2yr\n  =10000×(1.05)²=10000×1.1025=11025\nEx: Value=50000, depn=20%, T=2yr\n  =50000×(0.8)²=50000×0.64=32000",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_350",
