    {
      "id": "el_360",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 62,
      "y": 14417,
      "width": 232,
      "height": 18,
      "text": "Core SI Formula",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 14,
      "strokeColor": "#2f9e44",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 36000,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 360,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_21_0"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Core SI Formula",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_361",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 62,
      "y": 14439,
      "width": 273,
      "height": 203,
      "text": "SI = (P x R x T) / 100\n\nP = Principal (original sum)\nR = Rate of interest per annum (%)\nT = Time (in years)\nSI = Simple Interest\n\nWHY: R% means R per 100 per year.\n  Interest for 1yr = P×R/100.\n  For T years (simple) = P×R×T/100.\n\nEx: P=1000, R=10%, T=3yr\n  SI=1000×10×3/100=300",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 36100,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 361,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_21_0"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "SI = (P x R x T) / 100\n\nP = Principal (original sum)\nR = Rate of interest per annum (%)\nT = Time (in years)\nSI = Simple Interest\n\nWHY: R% means R per 100 per year.\n  Interest for 1yr = P×R/100.\n  For T years (simple) = P×R×T/100.\n\nEx: P=1000, R=10%, T=3yr\n  SI=1000×10×3/100=300",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_362",
      "type": "rectangle",
      "x": 530,
      "y": 14409,
      "width": 460,
      "height": 251,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#d0ebff",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
