    {
      "id": "el_369",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 62,
      "y": 14688,
      "width": 415,
      "height": 17,
      "text": "Multiplier / Doubling Formula",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#7048e8",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 36900,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 369,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_21_3"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Multiplier / Doubling Formula",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_370",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 62,
      "y": 14710,
      "width": 297,
      "height": 234,
      "text": "Sum becomes N times in T years:\n  (N - 1) x 100 = R x T\n\nDoubles:  R x T = 100\nTriples:  R x T = 200\nN times:  R x T = (N-1) x 100\n\nTime to double = 100/R\nTime to N times = (N-1) x 100/R\n\nWHY: N times means A=NP, so SI=(N-1)P.\n  (N-1)P = P×R×T/100 → R×T=(N-1)×100.\n\nEx: R=10%, double → T=100/10=10yr\n  Triple → T=200/10=20yr",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 37000,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 370,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_21_3"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Sum becomes N times in T years:\n  (N - 1) x 100 = R x T\n\nDoubles:  R x T = 100\nTriples:  R x T = 200\nN times:  R x T = (N-1) x 100\n\nTime to double = 100/R\nTime to N times = (N-1) x 100/R\n\nWHY: N times means A=NP, so SI=(N-1)P.\n  (N-1)P = P×R×T/100 → R×T=(N-1)×100.\n\nEx: R=10%, double → T=100/10=10yr\n  Triple → T=200/10=20yr",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_371",
