    {
      "id": "el_405",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 542,
      "y": 15842,
      "width": 432,
      "height": 18,
      "text": "Sample Space Quick Reference",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 14,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 40500,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 405,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_23_4"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Sample Space Quick Reference",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_406",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 542,
      "y": 15864,
      "width": 328,
      "height": 172,
      "text": "1 Coin = 2    n Coins = 2^n\n1 Die  = 6    2 Dice  = 36\n1 Deck = 52 cards (4 suits x 13)\n\nnCr heads in n tosses: P = nCr / 2^n\n2 dice sum=7: 6 ways, sum=2 or 12: 1 way\n\nWHY: Each coin has 2 outcomes, each die 6.\n  n coins = 2×2×...n times = 2^n.\n\nEx: 3 coins → 2^3=8 total outcomes",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 40600,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 406,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_23_4"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1 Coin = 2    n Coins = 2^n\n1 Die  = 6    2 Dice  = 36\n1 Deck = 52 cards (4 suits x 13)\n\nnCr heads in n tosses: P = nCr / 2^n\n2 dice sum=7: 6 ways, sum=2 or 12: 1 way\n\nWHY: Each coin has 2 outcomes, each die 6.\n  n coins = 2×2×...n times = 2^n.\n\nEx: 3 coins → 2^3=8 total outcomes",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
