    {
      "id": "el_432",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 542,
      "y": 16882,
      "width": 309,
      "height": 18,
      "text": "Master Angle Formula",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 14,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 43200,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 432,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_25_1"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Master Angle Formula",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_433",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 542,
      "y": 16904,
      "width": 351,
      "height": 203,
      "text": "Angle = |30H - 5.5M|\n\nH = hour (12-hr format)\nM = minutes\n\nIf result > 180 -> Angle = 360 - result\n(always take the SMALLER angle)\n\nWHY: Hour hand at 30H + 0.5M degrees from 12.\nMinute hand at 6M degrees from 12.\nAngle = |30H+0.5M - 6M| = |30H - 5.5M|.\n\nEx: At 3:30 → |90-165| = 75°",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 43300,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 433,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_25_1"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Angle = |30H - 5.5M|\n\nH = hour (12-hr format)\nM = minutes\n\nIf result > 180 -> Angle = 360 - result\n(always take the SMALLER angle)\n\nWHY: Hour hand at 30H + 0.5M degrees from 12.\nMinute hand at 6M degrees from 12.\nAngle = |30H+0.5M - 6M| = |30H - 5.5M|.\n\nEx: At 3:30 → |90-165| = 75°",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_434",
