    {
      "id": "el_435",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1022,
      "y": 16882,
      "width": 309,
      "height": 18,
      "text": "Hands at Angle theta",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 14,
      "strokeColor": "#e8590c",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 43500,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 435,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_25_2"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Hands at Angle theta",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_436",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1022,
      "y": 16904,
      "width": 422,
      "height": 188,
      "text": "Between H and (H+1) o'clock:\n  M = (30H + theta) x 2/11\n  M = (30H - theta) x 2/11\n\nTwo solutions (reject if M<0 or M>=60)\nOverlap: theta=0  Right: theta=90  Straight: theta=180\n\nWHY: Set |30H-5.5M|=theta, solve for M.\n5.5M = 30H +/- theta → M = (30H+/-theta)/5.5\nMultiply by 2/11 since 1/5.5 = 2/11.\n\nEx: Overlap at 4 → M=(120+0)×2/11=21 9/11",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 43600,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 436,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_25_2"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Between H and (H+1) o'clock:\n  M = (30H + theta) x 2/11\n  M = (30H - theta) x 2/11\n\nTwo solutions (reject if M<0 or M>=60)\nOverlap: theta=0  Right: theta=90  Straight: theta=180\n\nWHY: Set |30H-5.5M|=theta, solve for M.\n5.5M = 30H +/- theta → M = (30H+/-theta)/5.5\nMultiply by 2/11 since 1/5.5 = 2/11.\n\nEx: Overlap at 4 → M=(120+0)×2/11=21 9/11",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
