    {
      "id": "el_459",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 62,
      "y": 17808,
      "width": 436,
      "height": 15,
      "text": "Parallelogram, Rhombus, Trapezium",
      "fontSize": 12,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 12,
      "strokeColor": "#7048e8",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 45900,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 459,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_26_3"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Parallelogram, Rhombus, Trapezium",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_460",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 62,
      "y": 17830,
      "width": 297,
      "height": 203,
      "text": "Parallelogram: Area = base × height\n\nRhombus (diagonals d₁, d₂):\n  Area = (1/2) × d₁ × d₂\n  Side = (1/2)√(d₁² + d₂²)\n\nTrapezium (parallel sides a,b):\n  Area = (1/2)(a + b) × h\n\nWHY: Rhombus diagonals split it into 4\n  right triangles → total = d₁×d₂/2.\n\nEx: d₁=12, d₂=16 → Area=1/2×12×16=96",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 46000,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 460,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_26_3"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Parallelogram: Area = base × height\n\nRhombus (diagonals d₁, d₂):\n  Area = (1/2) × d₁ × d₂\n  Side = (1/2)√(d₁² + d₂²)\n\nTrapezium (parallel sides a,b):\n  Area = (1/2)(a + b) × h\n\nWHY: Rhombus diagonals split it into 4\n  right triangles → total = d₁×d₂/2.\n\nEx: d₁=12, d₂=16 → Area=1/2×12×16=96",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
