    {
      "id": "el_477",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1022,
      "y": 18161,
      "width": 339,
      "height": 18,
      "text": "Elevation & Depression",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 14,
      "strokeColor": "#e8590c",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 47700,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 477,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_27_2"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Elevation & Depression",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_478",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1022,
      "y": 18183,
      "width": 328,
      "height": 250,
      "text": "Angle of ELEVATION → looking UP\n  from horizontal to higher object\n\nAngle of DEPRESSION → looking DOWN\n  from horizontal to lower object\n\nKey: Depression from top\n   = Elevation from bottom\n   (alternate interior angles)\n\nWHY: Horizontal lines at top and bottom\n  are parallel → alternate interior angles\n  make depression angle = elevation angle.\n\nEx: Depression 30° from 50m tower\n  → d = 50/tan30° = 50√3 = 86.6m",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 47800,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 478,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_27_2"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Angle of ELEVATION → looking UP\n  from horizontal to higher object\n\nAngle of DEPRESSION → looking DOWN\n  from horizontal to lower object\n\nKey: Depression from top\n   = Elevation from bottom\n   (alternate interior angles)\n\nWHY: Horizontal lines at top and bottom\n  are parallel → alternate interior angles\n  make depression angle = elevation angle.\n\nEx: Depression 30° from 50m tower\n  → d = 50/tan30° = 50√3 = 86.6m",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_479",
