    {
      "id": "el_486",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1022,
      "y": 18479,
      "width": 339,
      "height": 18,
      "text": "Ladder / Kite / String",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 14,
      "strokeColor": "#0c8599",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 48600,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 486,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_27_5"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Ladder / Kite / String",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_487",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1022,
      "y": 18501,
      "width": 351,
      "height": 203,
      "text": "Ladder/String = HYPOTENUSE\n  sin θ = height / L\n  cos θ = distance / L\n  L = h / sin θ = d / cos θ\n\nKite height: h = L × sin θ\nWall height: h = L × sin θ\nFoot from wall: d = L × cos θ\n\nWHY: Ladder leans to form a right triangle;\n  it is always the hypotenuse (longest side).\n\nEx: L=10m, θ=60° → h=10×sin60°=5√3",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 48700,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 487,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_27_5"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Ladder/String = HYPOTENUSE\n  sin θ = height / L\n  cos θ = distance / L\n  L = h / sin θ = d / cos θ\n\nKite height: h = L × sin θ\nWall height: h = L × sin θ\nFoot from wall: d = L × cos θ\n\nWHY: Ladder leans to form a right triangle;\n  it is always the hypotenuse (longest side).\n\nEx: L=10m, θ=60° → h=10×sin60°=5√3",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
