    {
      "id": "el_535",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 542,
      "y": 20373,
      "width": 398,
      "height": 156,
      "text": "1. Write positions of original and coded letters\n2. Find difference for each letter\n3. Constant diff? -> Uniform shift\n4. Increasing diff? -> Position-based shift\n5. Sum = 27? -> Mirror/opposite coding\n6. Vowels != Consonants? -> Condition-based\n7. No letter pattern? -> Number/symbol substitution\n\nEx: CAT->FDW. Diffs: 3,3,3 -> uniform +3\n  HAT would be -> KDW (+3 each letter)",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 53500,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 535,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_30_4"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1. Write positions of original and coded letters\n2. Find difference for each letter\n3. Constant diff? -> Uniform shift\n4. Increasing diff? -> Position-based shift\n5. Sum = 27? -> Mirror/opposite coding\n6. Vowels != Consonants? -> Condition-based\n7. No letter pattern? -> Number/symbol substitution\n\nEx: CAT->FDW. Diffs: 3,3,3 -> uniform +3\n  HAT would be -> KDW (+3 each letter)",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
