    {
      "id": "el_546",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1022,
      "y": 20657,
      "width": 278,
      "height": 18,
      "text": "Shadow Rules (Sun)",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 14,
      "strokeColor": "#e8590c",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 54600,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 546,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_31_2"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Shadow Rules (Sun)",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_547",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1022,
      "y": 20679,
      "width": 390,
      "height": 219,
      "text": "MORNING: Sun=EAST  → Shadow=WEST\nEVENING: Sun=WEST  → Shadow=EAST\nNOON:    Sun overhead → No shadow\n\nMorning + shadow LEFT  → face NORTH\nMorning + shadow RIGHT → face SOUTH\nEvening: all rules REVERSE\n\nWHY: Shadow falls opposite the sun.\n  If sun is to your right (E), shadow is left (W).\n  Facing N: E=right, W=left → shadow left.\n\nEx: Evening, shadow to right → sun(W) is left\n  → facing SOUTH (reverse of morning rule)",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 54700,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 547,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_31_2"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "MORNING: Sun=EAST  → Shadow=WEST\nEVENING: Sun=WEST  → Shadow=EAST\nNOON:    Sun overhead → No shadow\n\nMorning + shadow LEFT  → face NORTH\nMorning + shadow RIGHT → face SOUTH\nEvening: all rules REVERSE\n\nWHY: Shadow falls opposite the sun.\n  If sun is to your right (E), shadow is left (W).\n  Facing N: E=right, W=left → shadow left.\n\nEx: Evening, shadow to right → sun(W) is left\n  → facing SOUTH (reverse of morning rule)",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
