    {
      "id": "el_564",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 62,
      "y": 21662,
      "width": 415,
      "height": 17,
      "text": "Argument & Cause-Effect Rules",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#7048e8",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 56400,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 564,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_32_3"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Argument & Cause-Effect Rules",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_565",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 62,
      "y": 21684,
      "width": 414,
      "height": 250,
      "text": "Strong Argument: Directly related, logical, realistic\nWeak Argument: Vague, emotional, personal, extreme\n\nCause-Effect types:\n  A causes B | B causes A | Independent\n  Common cause (3rd factor) | Both are effects\n\nTEST: \"Does A necessarily lead to B?\"\nCorrelation ≠ Causation!\n\nWHY: Strong arguments stand on evidence and\n  logic; weak ones rely on feelings or extremes.\n  Causation requires a mechanism, not just timing.\n\nEx: \"Umbrellas sold ↑ and floods ↑\" → NOT cause;\n  common cause = rain. Correlation ≠ Causation.",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 56500,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 565,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_32_3"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Strong Argument: Directly related, logical, realistic\nWeak Argument: Vague, emotional, personal, extreme\n\nCause-Effect types:\n  A causes B | B causes A | Independent\n  Common cause (3rd factor) | Both are effects\n\nTEST: \"Does A necessarily lead to B?\"\nCorrelation ≠ Causation!\n\nWHY: Strong arguments stand on evidence and\n  logic; weak ones rely on feelings or extremes.\n  Causation requires a mechanism, not just timing.\n\nEx: \"Umbrellas sold ↑ and floods ↑\" → NOT cause;\n  common cause = rain. Correlation ≠ Causation.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_566",
      "type": "rectangle",
      "x": 530,
