    {
      "id": "el_567",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 542,
      "y": 21662,
      "width": 401,
      "height": 18,
      "text": "Input-Output Machine Rules",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 14,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 56700,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 567,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_32_4"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Input-Output Machine Rules",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_568",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 542,
      "y": 21684,
      "width": 398,
      "height": 250,
      "text": "Step 1: Compare Input → Step I → what changed?\nStep 2: Compare Step I → Step II → what changed?\nStep 3: Identify PATTERN (sort, swap, rotate, etc.)\n\nCommon: smallest to front (selection sort),\n  swap adjacent (bubble sort), alternating ends\n\nTRICK: Count how many elements change per step\n  If only 1 moves → find which and where\n\nWHY: Each step applies the SAME rule. Identify\n  the rule from 2 consecutive steps, then apply\n  it forward to predict any future step.\n\nEx: Input: 7 3 5 1 → Step I: 1 7 3 5\n  Pattern: smallest moves to front (selection sort)",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 56800,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 568,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_32_4"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Step 1: Compare Input → Step I → what changed?\nStep 2: Compare Step I → Step II → what changed?\nStep 3: Identify PATTERN (sort, swap, rotate, etc.)\n\nCommon: smallest to front (selection sort),\n  swap adjacent (bubble sort), alternating ends\n\nTRICK: Count how many elements change per step\n  If only 1 moves → find which and where\n\nWHY: Each step applies the SAME rule. Identify\n  the rule from 2 consecutive steps, then apply\n  it forward to predict any future step.\n\nEx: Input: 7 3 5 1 → Step I: 1 7 3 5\n  Pattern: smallest moves to front (selection sort)",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
