    {
      "id": "el_627",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 542,
      "y": 23918,
      "width": 324,
      "height": 18,
      "text": "Venn Diagram Patterns",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 14,
      "strokeColor": "#2f9e44",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 62700,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 627,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_36_1"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Venn Diagram Patterns",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_628",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 542,
      "y": 23940,
      "width": 406,
      "height": 203,
      "text": "All A are B  → A circle INSIDE B circle\nSome A are B → A and B OVERLAP\nNo A are B   → A and B SEPARATE\nSome A not B → Part of A OUTSIDE B\n\nAll A are B: A ⊆ B (subset)\nNo A are B:  A ∩ B = {} (disjoint)\n\nWHY: Venn circles visually show set membership;\n  overlap = shared elements, separate = none shared.\n\nEx: All dogs are animals → (Dog) ⊂ (Animal)\n  No fish are birds → (Fish)  (Birds) apart",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 62800,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 628,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_36_1"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "All A are B  → A circle INSIDE B circle\nSome A are B → A and B OVERLAP\nNo A are B   → A and B SEPARATE\nSome A not B → Part of A OUTSIDE B\n\nAll A are B: A ⊆ B (subset)\nNo A are B:  A ∩ B = {} (disjoint)\n\nWHY: Venn circles visually show set membership;\n  overlap = shared elements, separate = none shared.\n\nEx: All dogs are animals → (Dog) ⊂ (Animal)\n  No fish are birds → (Fish)  (Birds) apart",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_629",
      "type": "rectangle",
      "x": 1010,
      "y": 23910,
      "width": 460,
      "height": 282,
      "strokeColor": "#e8590c",
      "backgroundColor": "#fff4e6",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
