    {
      "id": "el_630",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1022,
      "y": 23918,
      "width": 355,
      "height": 18,
      "text": "Valid Conclusion Chains",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 14,
      "strokeColor": "#e8590c",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 63000,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 630,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_36_2"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Valid Conclusion Chains",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_631",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1022,
      "y": 23940,
      "width": 336,
      "height": 234,
      "text": "All+All = All    (A+A=A)\nAll+No  = No     (A+E=E)\nSome+All = Some  (I+A=I)\nSome+No = Some-not (I+E=O)\n\nAll+Some = NO conclusion\nSome+Some = NO conclusion\nMiddle term MUST be distributed!\n\nWHY: The middle term links two sets;\n  it must cover all members (distributed)\n  so the chain is unbroken.\n\nEx: All A are B + All B are C → All A are C\n  (A⊂B, B⊂C → A⊂C, chain through B)",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 63100,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 631,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_36_2"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "All+All = All    (A+A=A)\nAll+No  = No     (A+E=E)\nSome+All = Some  (I+A=I)\nSome+No = Some-not (I+E=O)\n\nAll+Some = NO conclusion\nSome+Some = NO conclusion\nMiddle term MUST be distributed!\n\nWHY: The middle term links two sets;\n  it must cover all members (distributed)\n  so the chain is unbroken.\n\nEx: All A are B + All B are C → All A are C\n  (A⊂B, B⊂C → A⊂C, chain through B)",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_632",
