    {
      "id": "el_633",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 62,
      "y": 24220,
      "width": 247,
      "height": 18,
      "text": "Conversion Rules",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 14,
      "strokeColor": "#7048e8",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 63300,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 633,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_36_3"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Conversion Rules",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
    {
      "id": "el_634",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 62,
      "y": 24242,
      "width": 390,
      "height": 219,
      "text": "All A are B  → Some B are A (A→I)\nNo A are B   → No B are A   (E→E)\nSome A are B → Some B are A (I→I)\nSome A not B → NO conversion (O→X)\n\nTRAP: All A are B ≠ All B are A\nOnly: All A are B → Some B are A\n\nWHY: Conversion swaps subject & predicate.\n  Universal Aff. loses info (A⊂B ≠ B⊂A),\n  so only weaker I-type survives.\n\nEx: All cats are animals → Some animals are cats ✓\n  Some cats not dogs → CANNOT convert ✗",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 63400,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 634,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f_36_3"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "All A are B  → Some B are A (A→I)\nNo A are B   → No B are A   (E→E)\nSome A are B → Some B are A (I→I)\nSome A not B → NO conversion (O→X)\n\nTRAP: All A are B ≠ All B are A\nOnly: All A are B → Some B are A\n\nWHY: Conversion swaps subject & predicate.\n  Universal Aff. loses info (A⊂B ≠ B⊂A),\n  so only weaker I-type survives.\n\nEx: All cats are animals → Some animals are cats ✓\n  Some cats not dogs → CANNOT convert ✗",
      "autoResize": true,
